{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_28","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `org.fusesource.leveldbjni:leveldbjni-all:1.8` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2940-library-new-request-org.fusesource.leveldbjni-leveldbjni-all-1.8-1358573a\n\nThe most likely failing stage was native test verification feeding into metadata-fix, not initial file generation. The generated test `openDatabaseLoadsBundledNativeLibraryFromClasspath(Path)` repeatedly failed under `:nativeTest`; the clearest failure is in `logs/org.fusesource.leveldbjni:leveldbjni-all:1.8/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-28T15-12-58-855826Z.log`, which shows `java.lang.UnsatisfiedLinkError: org.fusesource.leveldbjni.internal.NativeOptions.init()V [symbol: Java_org_fusesource_leveldbjni_internal_NativeOptions_init ...]`. The metadata-fix and post-gen logs indicate the bundled `libleveldbjni.so` was found/extracted and `NativeOptions.init()` was already present in the native-image JNI registry, so this looks like native-image runtime linkage of the dynamically loaded HawtJNI/LevelDB library rather than a missing reachability-metadata entry. The follow-up intervention deleted the only generated test to get `./gradlew test` green, which matches the final metrics: failure status, `generated_loc: 0`, artifacts recorded as `test_file=None` / `metadata_file=None`, and dynamic-access coverage unavailable.\n\nPlease inspect `logs/org.fusesource.leveldbjni:leveldbjni-all:1.8/metadata-fix/codex.log`, `logs/org.fusesource.leveldbjni:leveldbjni-all:1.8/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-06-28T15-33-26-252399Z.log`, `logs/org.fusesource.leveldbjni:leveldbjni-all:1.8/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-28T15-12-58-855826Z.log`, `logs/org.fusesource.leveldbjni:leveldbjni-all:1.8/native-test-verify/cycle-23-finalizedTest-2026-06-28T15-11-29-113301Z.log`, `post-gen-interventions/org.fusesource.leveldbjni_leveldbjni-all_1.8.md`, and `stats/org.fusesource.leveldbjni/leveldbjni-all/1.8/execution-metrics.json`.\n\nNext steps:\n- Reproduce from the preserved branch and decide whether `leveldbjni-all` can support native-image runtime loading of its bundled HawtJNI/LevelDB shared library at all, or whether this library should be treated as unsupported for a new-library submission.\n- If support is intended, debug the JNI linkage path around `org.fusesource.hawtjni.runtime.Library.load()` and `org.fusesource.leveldbjni.internal.NativeOptions.init()`; metadata/resource registration alone did not make the native test pass.\n- Either replace the deleted database-opening test with a different library-specific native-image-safe test, or close/reject the request if every meaningful test requires the unsupported bundled JNI loading path."}}
